“Indigenous peoples have become the most marginalized and vulnerable group in
the country of Bangladesh in its thirty eight years of independence,”
[informs](http://monirul.wordpress.com/2010/10/02/vanishing-identity-2/)
photojournalist and photo-blogger _Monirul Alam_. He has started a project
which involves a visual and narrative documentation of the Indigenous people
expressing their daily life, their cultural practices and integration in the
society.

